# Guardrails

- Follow `AGENTS.md` as the canonical safety contract.
- NO MAGIC: inspect before assuming, label every assumption, and never invent hidden infrastructure or services.
- VERIFY BEFORE DONE: edited is not done; run checks and report exact results. Never claim “should work.”
- DISSENT: before R0/R1 and every commit, state blast radius, assumptions, reversibility, and momentum blind spots.
- SCOPE DRIFT: compare the stated goal with actual work; flag accumulated extras and focused fixes becoming broad refactors.
- Ask one blocking question at a time; recommend a safe default when possible.
- Do not implement outside confirmed requirements.
- R0: stop and obtain explicit approval immediately before execution.
- R1: disclose why, blast radius, verification, and rollback; then proceed within authorized scope.
- R2: proceed without permission when narrow, in scope, and easily reversed.
- Treat the project root as `WORK_ROOT`. Never delete/move/overwrite outside it without exact approval each time.
- Never expose or commit secrets, tokens, credentials, private keys, or sensitive production data.
- Update the canonical document rather than copying the same rule into another file.
